es&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt; actions/checkout@v1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;token-line&quot; style=&quot;color:#d6deeb&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line-number-style&quot;&gt;13&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token key atrule&quot;&gt;uses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt; enriikke/gatsby&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;gh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;pages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;action@v2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;token-line&quot; style=&quot;color:#d6deeb&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line-number-style&quot;&gt;14&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token key atrule&quot;&gt;with&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;token-line&quot; style=&quot;color:#d6deeb&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line-number-style&quot;&gt;15&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;          &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token key atrule&quot;&gt;access-token&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt; $&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt; secrets.ACCESS_TOKEN &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;token-line&quot; style=&quot;color:#d6deeb&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line-number-style&quot;&gt;16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;          &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token key atrule&quot;&gt;deploy-branch&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt; gh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(199, 146, 234)&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;pages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Before you go and push this change, note that it requires a secret named &lt;code class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;ACCESS_TOKEN&lt;/code&gt;. It needs that token to push changes to your repo.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;You&amp;#x27;ll need to generate a personal access token with &lt;code class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;repo&lt;/code&gt; scope. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.github.com/en/github/authenticating-to-github/creating-a-personal-access-token&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; for instructions on how to do that. Copy the token, open your repository&amp;#x27;s settings, go to the &amp;quot;Secrets&amp;quot; tab, and create a new secret named &lt;code class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;ACCESS_TOKEN&lt;/code&gt; with the token you copied.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;max-width:960px&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot; style=&quot;padding-bottom:64.99999999999999%;position:relative;bottom:0;left:0;background-image:url(&amp;#x27;data:image/png;base64,&amp;#x27;);background-size:cover;display:block&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image css-0&quot; alt=&quot;Adding GitHub secret&quot; title=&quot;Adding GitHub secret&quot; src=&quot;/static/64cf4b6d06b130b5f5df335e733bc4c4/7d769/screenshot_secret.png&quot; srcSet=&quot;/static/64cf4b6d06b130b5f5df335e733bc4c4/5243c/screenshot_secret.png 240w,/static/64cf4b6d06b130b5f5df335e733bc4c4/ab158/screenshot_secret.png 480w,/static/64cf4b6d06b130b5f5df335e733bc4c4/7d769/screenshot_secret.png 960w,/static/64cf4b6d06b130b5f5df335e733bc4c4/74f55/screenshot_secret.png 1245w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px&quot; style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;With the secret in place, go ahead and push those changes. Go to the &amp;quot;Actions&amp;quot; tab in GitHub and you can watch the build in action. Assuming it completes successfully, you&amp;#x27;ll find there&amp;#x27;s a new &lt;code class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;gh-pages&lt;/code&gt; branch with your compiled website (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mattbun/mattbun.github.io/tree/gh-pages&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;like this&lt;/a&gt;). We&amp;#x27;re almost there!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;css-170hkfz&quot;&gt;Step 4: Enable GitHub Pages&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Now you just need to &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.github.com/en/github/working-with-github-pages/configuring-a-publishing-source-for-your-github-pages-site&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;enable Github Pages&lt;/a&gt; on this repository. Click the Settings tab and scroll all the way down to the &amp;quot;GitHub Pages&amp;quot; section. Choose your new &lt;code class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;gh-pages&lt;/code&gt; branch and hit save!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;max-width:883px&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot; style=&quot;padding-bottom:17.5%;position:relative;bottom:0;left:0;background-image:url(&amp;#x27;data:image/png;base64,&amp;#x27;);background-size:cover;display:block&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image css-0&quot; alt=&quot;Enabling GitHub Pages&quot; title=&quot;Enabling GitHub Pages&quot; src=&quot;/static/e744dbbca380aea63d54b60b1d442b7c/fb35e/screenshot_pages.png&quot; srcSet=&quot;/static/e744dbbca380aea63d54b60b1d442b7c/5243c/screenshot_pages.png 240w,/static/e744dbbca380aea63d54b60b1d442b7c/ab158/screenshot_pages.png 480w,/static/e744dbbca380aea63d54b60b1d442b7c/fb35e/screenshot_pages.png 883w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 883px) 100vw, 883px&quot; style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;css-170hkfz&quot;&gt;Step 5: Try it Out!&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;That should be it! Open up your website at &lt;code class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;-github.io&lt;/code&gt; and it should be up and running! ðŸŽ‰ðŸ’ƒ&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;css-170hkfz&quot;&gt;Bonus: Using a Custom Domain&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;In addition to &lt;a href=&quot;https://mattbun.github.io&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;mattbun.github.io&lt;/a&gt;, I updated my domain &lt;a href=&quot;https://rathbun.dev&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;rathbun.dev&lt;/a&gt; to point to it as well. &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.github.com/en/github/working-with-github-pages/managing-a-custom-domain-for-your-github-pages-site#configuring-an-apex-domain&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;These instructions&lt;/a&gt; show you how to do it. My domain is registered through Google Domains and my DNS settings there look something like this:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;max-width:960px&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot; style=&quot;padding-bottom:45.416666666666664%;position:relative;bottom:0;left:0;background-image:url(&amp;#x27;data:image/png;base64,&amp;#x27;);background-size:cover;display:block&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image css-0&quot; alt=&quot;Configuring DNS in Google Domains&quot; title=&quot;Configuring DNS in Google Domains&quot; src=&quot;/static/ae18c680507372fdd3895a6f6dad37ca/7d769/screenshot_dns.png&quot; srcSet=&quot;/static/ae18c680507372fdd3895a6f6dad37ca/5243c/screenshot_dns.png 240w,/static/ae18c680507372fdd3895a6f6dad37ca/ab158/screenshot_dns.png 480w,/static/ae18c680507372fdd3895a6f6dad37ca/7d769/screenshot_dns.png 960w,/static/ae18c680507372fdd3895a6f6dad37ca/28aea/screenshot_dns.png 990w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px&quot; style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Be sure to put your domain name in a file named &lt;code class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;CNAME&lt;/code&gt; in the root directory on your master branch. GitHub will try to add it to your &lt;code class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;gh-pages&lt;/code&gt; branch but the Gatsby Publish action will overwrite it. If you put it in master, the action &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/marketplace/actions/gatsby-publish#cname&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;will copy the file over when it deploys&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item></channel></rss>